me":"td","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Adjust knobs to keep adjusting model weights"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"üéØ Let‚Äôs talk a bit more about parametric learning"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A naive way of describing parametric learning would be to say it‚Äôs a trial and error based method. For example, you have several photos of dogs, and you are given another photo(the input) and told to match it with the existing photos. You‚Äôll keep comparing it with each and every photo until you find the correct one. This is trial and error based. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Now let‚Äôs go a bit deeper into supervised parametric learning as well which is something I‚Äôll talk about in further blogs as well.\nThere are 3 major steps to supervised parametric learning:\nPrediction: The first step would be to give the input to the algorithm and get it‚Äôs prediction on the data. You‚Äôll be thinking how did we jump into prediction directly without training the model at all. Therein comes  the second step.\nComparison with the true value: Now we‚Äôll compare the predicted value of the algorithm with the true value that we should have gotten. In this step we‚Äôll calculate the error between the predicted and actual value. Unless the error is 0, we‚Äôll proceed to the next and final step.\nLearning the pattern: In this step, we will do the ‚Äútraining‚Äù. We will adjust the model weights(turn the knobs) such that the prediction would have been closer to the true value."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"From the next blog, we‚Äôll get into the details about how these 3 steps actually work and get our hands dirty with some code as well. "}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-teach-machines/","prefix":"2021-01-21"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How To Teach Machines","author":"Yash Khare","tags":["ml from scratch"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/blog/static/4b89fce7bc31e2146fdb42e6867fee35/c83a6/featured.jpg"}}}},"parent":{"__typename":"File","modifiedTime":"2021-03-11"}},"authornote":{"id":"d068915d-d209-5a47-ba22-eed3c3f3665e","html":"<p><strong>Mr. Gatsby</strong> Proin ornare ligula eu tellus tempus elementum. Aenean <a href=\"/blog/\">bibendum</a> iaculis mi, nec blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus. Blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus.</p>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"strong","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Mr. Gatsby"}]},{"type":"text","value":" Proin ornare ligula eu tellus tempus elementum. Aenean "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/blog/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"bibendum"}]},{"type":"text","value":" iaculis mi, nec blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus. Blandit lacus interdum vitae. Vestibulum non nibh risus, a scelerisque purus."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-teach-machines/","next":{"id":"625b6df4-3d68-5ed1-bbb6-4f1779b934fa","excerpt":"The MLH Fellowship finally came to an end on 21st December 2020. It was an amazing 3 months I spent as a part of the first ever Explorer‚Ä¶","fields":{"slug":"/mlh-fellowship-graduation/","prefix":"2021-01-14","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"MLH Fellowship(Fall 2020): Graduation","tags":["Major League Hacking: Fellowship"],"cover":{"children":[{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3